# FastAPI Conventions

- One router per domain (e.g. `documents`, `llm`, `health`); mount under a clear prefix (`/documents`, `/llm`).
- Use Pydantic models for request/response bodies; name them with `Request`/`Response` suffix (e.g. `CompletionRequest`, `CompletionResponse`).
- Prefer dependency injection for `Settings` and shared clients; use `Depends(get_settings)` when needed.
- Return 4xx for client errors (400 validation, 404 not found, 422 unprocessable) and 5xx for server/upstream failures (502 when LLM or converter fails).

## Endpoints

```python
# BAD: raw dict, no validation
@router.post("/items")
async def items(body: dict):
    return {"items": body["ids"][:1]}

# GOOD: Pydantic model, typed response
class ItemCreate(BaseModel):
    name: str

class ItemResponse(BaseModel):
    id: str
    label: str

@router.post("/items", response_model=list[ItemResponse])
async def create_item(req: ItemCreate) -> list[ItemResponse]:
    return [ItemResponse(id="1", label=req.name)]
```

For `/chunk`, use file upload or URL plus `ChunkResponse` with `list[ChunkItem]` (FFP pipeline output), not a raw text body.

- Use `UploadFile = File(...)` for file uploads; read content with `await file.read()` and pass bytes to services.
